<HEADLINE> Injured Referee Replaced for Bayer-Real Game </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Kim Nilsson of Denmark will replace
injured Anders Frisk of Sweden to officiate Wednesday's European
Cup quarter-final match between Bayer Leverkusen and Real Madrid,
UEFA said on Monday.
</P>
<P>
UEFA added that the match would mark a departure from the
normal practice of a refereeing team all coming from the same
country.
</P>
<P>
This was because assistant referee Mikael Nilsson of Sweden was
due to officiate at the World Cup finals in the summer and UEFA
wanted all officials for that tournament to get as much experience
as possible in the final phases of the continental club
competitions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
