<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Pakistan Conducts National Census </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan on Monday began its
gigantic national census to enumerate the country's existing
population and garner national housing data.
</P>
<P>
As many as 280,000 civilian and army personnel are engaged in
conducting the fifth National Population and Housing Census on
March 2-18, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif said in a message on Sunday that
the census was inevitable for future planning and development of
the country.
</P>
<P>
He said the massive task, which is in the best national
interests, should be considered above any provincialism,
parochialism and personal interests.
</P>
<P>
The federal cabinet Saturday decided to give the go-ahead to
the long-awaited census as scheduled, contrary to days of
speculation that it would be put off again.
</P>
<P>
Pakistan conducted its last national census in 1981. But the
successive governments had not carried out one since then despite
a constitutional provision stipulating that a census should be
held every 10 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
