<HEADLINE> Nepal to Implement Irrigation Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Nepal will implement an
irrigation project in the western part of the country to raise
agricultural production and farmers' income, the official RSS news
agency said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The project, financed by a World Bank loan, will bring under
irrigation 60,000 hectares of land in 40 of the country's 75
districts.
</P>
<P>
At a workshop here Monday, World Bank country director Hans M.
Rothenbuhler stressed the need to expand irrigation in a country
like Nepal to increase agricultural production.
</P>
<P>
Dwarikanath Dhungel, secretary at the Ministry for Water
Resources, said the government has adopted a 20-year Agriculture
Perspective Plan which accords priority to the expansion of
irrigation facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
