<HEADLINE> Ethiopians Mark Adwa Victory Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopians throughout the
country Monday celebrated the 102nd anniversary of victory of Adwa
over the Italian invaders.
</P>
<P>
In the capital city of Addis Ababa, this victory day was
marked at the Menelik square in the presence of patriots of the
anti-colonial resistance and a huge crowd -- residents of Addis
Ababa.
</P>
<P>
Dawit Yohannes, Speaker of the House of People's
Representatives laid wreath of flowers on the Menelik monument.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the ceremony Monday morning, Chairman of the
Ethiopian Patriots Association Assefa Bayu said Adwa is the
victory of both Ethiopia and Africa. He called on the young
generation to keep the spirit of Adwa intact.
</P>
<P>
Celebrations of the Adwa victory day were held with all the
pomp throughout the country Monday, according to the Ethiopian
News Agency.
</P>
<P>
On March 1, 1986, Ethiopian soldiers led by Emperor Menelik ii
defeated 15,000 well-equipped Italian invaders at Adwa in
northern Ethiopia. The famous battle of Adwa forced the Italian
aggressors to recognize Ethiopia as a sovereign independent
state.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia celebrates the Adwa victory day every year on March 2
and March 2 is a public holiday for Ethiopians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
