<HEADLINE> Taiwan Urged to Respond to Appeal for Cross-Strait Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The members of the Ninth National
Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) are concerned with the talks across the Taiwan
strait, according to a CPPCC spokesman.
</P>
<P>
"Under the principle of one China, it is an essential for
further expanding the across-strait relations to officially put an
end to the hostilities across the Taiwan Straits," said Liang
Jinquan, spokesman for the First Session of the Ninth CPPC
National Committee, at a press conference held here today.
</P>
<P>
The First Session of the Ninth CPPCC National Committee will be
held tomorrow and run through March 14.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-based Association for Relations Across the Taiwan
Straits (ARATS) and the Straits Exchange Foundation (SEF) from
Taiwan should make prompt programmatic arrangements for political
talks and, on this basis, resume economic and routine business
talks.
</P>
<P>
"ARATS sent a formal message a week ago and we expect a timely
response from Taiwan side," said Liang.
</P>
<P>
The great concept of "one country, two systems" put forward by
Deng Xiaoping when he was the chairman of the Fifth CPPCC National
Conference, has been turned into a reality in Hong Kong, noted
Liang.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, it is certain that the motherland's reunification
will be accomplished under the guidance of "one country, two
systems", "reunification through peaceful means" set forth by Deng
Xiaoping and the Eight-Point proposal for promoting the
across-strait relations put forward by Jiang Zemin, and through
concerted efforts by people across the straits, the spokesman
said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
