<HEADLINE> Rwandan Vice-president Ends Visit to Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Rwandan Vice-President Paul
Kagami left here Monday, ending a two-day official visit after
talks with Ethiopian officials on bilateral ties and regional
situation.
</P>
<P>
The Ethiopian News Agency reported that Kagami had talks with
Ethiopian Prime Minister Meles Zenawi on bilateral issues. But
the report did not disclose details of the talks between the two
sides.
</P>
<P>
Kagami sent troops to fight in former Zaire to back L. Kabila
in toppling late President Mobutu Sese Seko last May. And east
and central African leaders met in Kampala last month to discuss
whether to lift their economic sanctions against Burundi.
</P>
<P>
Sources here said Kagami came to brief Meles on the regional
situation in the Great Lakes region.
</P>
<P>
The Rwandan vice-president arrived here Sunday. He was
welcomed and seen off at the airport by Tefera Waluwa, Ethiopian
Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Defense. 
</P>
