<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Commission of Status of Women to Hold 42nd Session </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Discussions on the human
rights of women, the girl child, women and armed conflict, and
violence against women will be the main focus of the forty-second
session of the Commission on the Status of Women, to held at
Headquarters from 2 to 13 March.
</P>
<P>
The Commission, which is a subsidiary body of the Economic and
Social Council, is charged with monitoring implementation of the
Beijing Declaration and Platform for Action, which is a agenda for
Womem's empowerment.
</P>
<P>
Under its multi-year program of work until 2000, the
Commission focuses on some of the 12 critical areas of concern to
women contained in the Beijing Platform for Action, adopted at the
1995 Fourth World Conference on Woman.
</P>
<P>
This year's topics -- human rights of women, the girl child,
women and armed conflict, and violence against women -- will be
debated by expert panels, resulting in action-oriented
recommendations for adoption by the Commission. 
</P>
</TEXT>
