<HEADLINE> Turkey Urges Syria to Cooperate in Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Turkey called for Syria's
cooperation on Monday in fighting terrorism to secure a good
environment for them.
</P>
<P>
"We have expressed our expectations to the Syrian side
regarding cooperation in fighting terrorism," Sermet Atacanli,
Turkish Foreign Ministry Deputy Spokesman told a weekly press
conference.
</P>
<P>
Atacanli said that during his visit last week to Syria, Turkish
Foreign Ministry official Aykut Chetirge discussed the issue with
the Syrian side.
</P>
<P>
But he did not elaborate.
</P>
<P>
Chetirge's visit followed a statement made by Syrian Foreign
Minister Farouq Al-Sharaa that Damascus would like to have a
dialogue with the Turkish government.
</P>
<P>
Describing the visit as "a positive step," Atacanli said the
contact was in the direction of improving the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Although the disputes are remaining unsolved, the visit has
opened up a channel for starting dialogues between the two
countries, he added.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Syria, two Muslim neighbors, have long shared a
bitter relationship due to a number of disputes, including the
distribution of water resources and the issue of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Ankara has accused Damascus of supporting its outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party, which has been fighting the Turkish government for
autonomy in the southeastern areas.
</P>
<P>
Syria, however, has denied the charge.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish spokesman said that Chetirge briefed Syrian
officials on the Turkish-Israeli ties, saying that Turkey
understands the sensitivity of the Arab world, including Syria,
regarding the issue.
</P>
<P>
"We have made it very clear that our relations with Israel is
not aimed at any third party," said Atacanli, adding that the
Turkish-Israeli cooperation is of bilateral nature. 
</P>
