<HEADLINE> Iranian Border Guards Kill 9 MKO Members </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Iranian border guards on Sunday
killed nine members of the outlawed Mujahideen Khalq Organization
(MKO) and wounded several others when they attempted to infiltrate
into the country, reported the official news agency IRNA.
</P>
<P>
IRNA quoted the information department of the western province
of Ilam that the MKO members clashed with border guards while they
tried to cross into the country for "sabotage operations."
</P>
<P>
The group had infiltrated into Iranian soil in collaboration
with Iraqi regime, the information department said, adding the MKO
members were carrying Klashinkov rifles, rocket propeller
grenades, machine-guns and wireless communications.
</P>
<P>
One Iranian border guard was also killed in the gunfire, the
report added.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian border guards have busted about 30 MKO members
grouped in six teams. The MKO, one of the main political groups
which fought against the late shah's regime, was outlawed in the
early 1980s due to serious political disputes with the Islamic
leadership of the country.
</P>
<P>
During the past years, particularly after the Iran-Iraq war
(1980-88), the group launched military attacks on Iranian
interests throughout the worlds, forcing Tehran to take several
air raids on its bases in northern Iraq. 
</P>
</TEXT>
