<HEADLINE> German Gross Wins World Cup Biathlon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Ricco Gross of Germany retained his
slim World Cup lead with a perfect shooting record in a victory of
20-kilometer race in Pokljuka of Slovenia on Tuesday, the first
biathlon event after the Winter Olympics in Nagano.
</P>
<P>
Gross, who anchored Germany to the relay gold but won on
individual medal in Nagano, clocked in 53 minutes 51 second to
beat Norway's Egil Gjelland by 2.5 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Neither man had any misses on the four five-shot ranges.
</P>
<P>
Another Norwegian, Ole Einar Bjoerndalen, the Olympic
10-Kilometers champion, finished third, 47.1 seconds behind Gross.
</P>
<P>
Gross has 224 points in World Cup standings and leads
Bjoerndalen by 10. 
</P>
</TEXT>
