<HEADLINE> Fluke-Hewlett Launches Sales Alliance in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- U.S-based companies Fluke
Corporation and Hewlett Packard announced today that the first
Asian operations of the Fluke-Hewlett distribution and marketing
alliance will be launched in China.
</P>
<P>
The agreement between Fluke and Hewlett Packard will establish
a sales alliance in China, with the former marketing the latter's
basic instrument line through established sales channels. Hewlett
Packard will in turn market Fluke's compact electronic testing
instruments through its Chinese distributors.
</P>
<P>
"The two companies share a multifaceted relationship. We have
well established reciprocal customer relationships and jointed
sales channels, However, we are also competitors in terms of
various products lines," according to Fluke Chairman and CEO Bill
Oarzybok.
</P>
<P>
Fluke has selected two Chinese companies for distributorships,
and additional distributors will join the sales team in the near
future, said Oarzybok.
</P>
<P>
He said that Fluke has recorded marginal business growth in
China over the past few years, but noted that China is one of the
fastest growing markets for the company's products. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
