<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Real Estate Agents in Guangzhou Put under Stricter Controls </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Guangzhou, capital of south
China'a Guangdong Province, has made new regulations for real
estate agents to improve the real estate market.
</P>
<P>
Because of its growing property market, Guangzhou has about
1,000 property agents, but only 450 have government department
certification. The new rules, which take effect on March 1, will
require real estate agency employees to obtain proper
certification to qualify for work in the field.
</P>
<P>
Agents will fall into three categories, the highest of which
will need at least a million yuan (120,000 US dollars) in
operating funds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
