<HEADLINE> Kidnappers Release Russian Soccer Chief's Child </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 3 (Xinhua) - Kidnappers in southern Russia have
freed the 11-year-old daughter of the president of Russian premier
division soccer club Vladikavkaz Alania, police said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
A police spokesman in the volatile region of North Ossetia said
Zalina Bitarova was at home with her parents after being held for
ransom for 66 days by unidentified kidnappers.
</P>
<P>
The girl was seized from outside her school in December.
kidnappers had demanded three million U.S. dollars for her release
but later scaled down their demands, according to the Interfax
news agency.
</P>
<P>
Batraz Bitarov is president of Alania Vladikavkaz, based in the
region's main city. The club won the Russian premier league
championship in 1995, but dropped to the 10th place last year.
</P>
</TEXT>
