<HEADLINE> Peasant Woman Proud of Being NPC Deputy for Nine Terms </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Shen Jilan, a peasant woman from
Shanxi Province and a deputy to the Ninth National People's
Congress (NPC), said she feels proud to serve as an NPC deputy for
nine terms.
</P>
<P>
Shen was elected a deputy to the First NPC in 1954 when the
people's congress system was established. And she has been elected
to the NPC of all succeeding terms ever then. She is here to
attend the Ninth NPC's first session, which is to begin on coming
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
During the years, Shen has been cited as a model worker by
central and local governments on many occasions.
</P>
<P>
"Only under the leadership of the Communist Party can we
ordinary peasants have the right to be masters of our own
affairs," she said.
</P>
<P>
Over the years, she has put forward many proposals relating to
agriculture, water conservation and tree planting. Many of her
proposals have attracted the attention of the government, she said.
</P>
<P>
At the Fourth Session of the Eighth NPC in 1996, President
Jiang Zemin joined discussions with deputies from Shanxi
Province. Shen Jilan talked about the importance of having
enough food grains and the importance of agriculture as
peasants' lifeblood.
</P>
<P>
Shaking hands with her, the president said he appreciated her
proposal, Shen Jilan recalled.
</P>
<P>
"I think the people's congress system is the best form of
democracy, through which people can express their opinions to the
central authorities while the central authorities work out major
policies on the basis of public opinion," the deputy said.
</P>
<P>
"As long as I serve as a deputy to the NPC, I will speak on
behalf of the people," she said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
