<HEADLINE> Pakistan Seeks Close Cooperation With Russia on </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif said
on Tuesday that Pakistan considers Russia as an important country
and wishes to develop close friendly relations with it for peace
and progress in the region.
</P>
<P>
During talks with visiting Russian Deputy Foreign Minister
Grigory Karasin, Sharif said Russia is an important neighbor of
Pakistan and the two countries can work together to seek a
peaceful solution to of the Afghan problem by bringing the warring
parties to the negotiating table.
</P>
<P>
Sharif also hoped that in line with the global trends, economic
relations between Pakistan and Russia would assume the center
stage.
</P>
<P>
Sharif informed Karasin of the steps Pakistan has taken for a
comprehensive political settlement of the conflict in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
Sharif stressed that the international community, particularly
countries like Russia, have an important role to play in bringing
about a peaceful settlement of the Afghan issue.
</P>
<P>
Karasin said Russia has a keen interest in upgrading the
existing bilateral relations with Pakistan. He called upon the two
sides to initiate measures to enhance the existing economic
cooperation to the benefit of both countries. 
</P>
