</P>
<P>
GENEVA -- The weather phenomenon known as El Nino has passed
its peak in some areas like Australia, but its influence is likely
to continue well into May in some other areas.
</P>
<P>
The destructive phenomenon, said the World Meteorological
Organization (WMO) in its special "El Nino Update" released here
Tuesday, dominated climatic conditions in the last two
years. (WMO-El Nino)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister Tariq Aziz said Tuesday
that Iraq will observe the agreement with U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan on peacefully ending the crisis over weapons
inspection, Iraqi News Agency (INA) reported.
</P>
<P>
