signature to the agreement will honor its commitment and respect
U.N. Security Council resolutions concerning the
agreement. (Iraq-UN-Agreement)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
SEOUL -- South Korean President Kim Dae-jung appointed a
controversial figure as acting prime minister Tuesday, a day after
the parliament failed to vote over the same person's nomination as
prime minister.
</P>
<P>
"I had no choice but to urgently appoint Kim Jong-pil as acting
prime minister," President Kim told his first press conference
since he took office last Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The vote by the National Assembly, or parliament, on the
nomination was suspended Monday when lawmakers from the ruling
coalition of the National Congress, New Politics and United
Liberal Democrats physically clashed with those from the
opposition Grand National Party (GNP). (S. Korea-Appointment)
</P>
