<HEADLINE> Yunnan Thermal Power Plant Enters Operations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- A new thermal power plant in
Qujing, southwest China's Yunnan Province, recently entered
operations following successful trial operations of its first
300,000 kw generator.
</P>
<P>
The plant plans to invest 2.94 billion yuan to install two
300,000 kw generators during the first phase construction. A
second 300,000 kw generator is expected to enter operations by the
end of the year.
</P>
<P>
The plant is expected to ease power shortages which are
especially pronounced during the dry season.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan's installed generating capacity hit 6.18 million kw by
the end of 1997, with hydroelectric facilities accounting for over
70 percent of the total.
</P>
<P>
The province supplies power to other provinces during the rainy
season, but nonetheless faces severe local power shortages during
the dry season. The undesirable situation has prompted the
province to accelerate the construction of thermal power plants.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
