<HEADLINE> Brunei's Sultan to Visit Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Brunei's Sultan Sir Muda Hassanal
Bolkiah is to arrive here Wednesday night for a two-day private
visit to the Philippines, the Philippine News Agency reported on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, the sultan will meet Philippine President
Fidel Ramos to discuss the proposed trading system among members
of the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN) using
regional currencies instead of the U.S. dollar.
</P>
<P>
The president and the sultan are also expected to discuss the
two countries' bilateral relations, especially economic
cooperation, trade and investment in the wake of the regional
financial turmoil.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Press Secretary Hector Villanueva said the sultan's
trip to Manila is "more of a goodwill visit because the sultan
wants to reciprocate previous visits of the president to Brunei."
</P>
<P>
Ramos went to Bandar Seri Begawan, Brunei's capital in October
1992 for a social visit, and he paid a state visit to Brunei in
August 1994. Two years later, Ramos was there acting as one of the
principal sponsors at the wedding of the sultan's eldest daughter.
</P>
<P>
Sultan Bolkiah visited Manila in 1991 at the invitation of
former president Corazon Aquino, and in November 1996 for the
fourth Asia- Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) Leaders' informal
meeting. 
</P>
