<HEADLINE> Leaders of NPC HK Delegation Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong delegation to the
Ninth National People's Congress (NPC) elected an educator and a
lawyer its leader and deputy leader here today.
</P>
<P>
Ng Hong-mun and Maria Tam Wai-chu were made respectively leader
and deputy leader of Hong Kong's first independent NPC delegation
through a vote at the delegaton's first meeting this afternoon.
The delegation is here to attend the NPC's first session, which is
to begin on coming Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"This is the first time that Hong Kong sends its own NPC
delegation to participate in managing state affairs," said Ng
Hong-mun after the election. "I expect our delegation to have a
good performance at the NPC session."
</P>
<P>
A middle school supervisor, the 71-year-old Ng has been an NPC
deputy since 1975. Maria Tam Wai-chu is a lawyer and took part in
drafting the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region.
</P>
<P>
With the death of one deputy not long ago, the Hong Kong
delegation now has 35 members. 
</P>
