<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Port of Entry Opens on Sino-Russian Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HOHHOT, March 3 (Xinhua) -- A new highway port of entry opened
earlier this week on the Sino-Russian border.
</P>
<P>
The facility links international highways leading to Manzhouli
in the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region and the Russian city of
Zabajkal'jesk City. The port features eight lanes capable of
handling one million tons of cargo and 1.2 million passengers
annually. First phase construction was completed at a cost of 35
million yuan (4.22 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Russia invested 30 million US dollars for construction
of the new port facility.
</P>
<P>
Manzhouli is a major border city linking China with the
Commonwealth of Independent States and countries in eastern
Europe. The port was constructed to relieve the stress of the
600,000 tons of cargo and 800,000 people handled by other ports of
entry in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
