<HEADLINE> Shanghai's Pudong Has 5,000 Overseas-Backed Ventures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The number of overseas-financed
businesses in Pudong New Area of east China's Shanghai amounts to
5,000 as Shanghai Molex Joints Corp., a solely U.S. financed
venture, settled in the Waigaoqiao Free Trade Zone on Feb. 26.
</P>
<P>
Overseas investment has poured in at a daily rate of 8.3
million U.S. dollars since the Pudong New Area was announced in
April of 1990, said local sources.
</P>
<P>
The overseas-financed companies -- which are generally
large-scale with improved structure, highly advanced technology
and high paid-in investment rate -- have an aggregate investment
of 24 billion dollars, involving a contractual use of 15.6 billion
dollars of overseas funds.
</P>
<P>
The Jinqiao Export Processing Zone of Pudong, for instance, has
approved the establishment of 302 projects which involve a total
investment of 7.15 billion dollars. And 158 of the approved
projects have begun production. They have generated 18 billion
yuan of output value.
</P>
<P>
The Jinqiao zone, which has emerged as an industrial town from
former farmland and is now capable of producing such products as
modern telecommunications equipment, micro-electronics, cars and
components. The zone is expected to generate 100 billion yuan of
output value in five years.
</P>
<P>
Local officials attributed their success in attracting overseas
funds to the their strict implementation of investment policies
while concentrating greater efforts on improving the environment
for local investment. 
</P>
</TEXT>
