<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
Tuesday approved the release of 3 million pesos (75,000 U.S.
dollars) for ongoing emergency operations to contain a malaria
outbreak in the southern Philippines.
</P>
<P>
Ramos approved the calamity fund after he received an update
report on the malaria outbreak in Siasi town, the southern
province of Sulu, a news release from the Presidential Palace
said.
</P>
<P>
Medical teams sent to the area reported that 133 patients had
died while 26 other were in serious conditions as of February 25.
</P>
<P>
