<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 13:41 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Israeli Jets Strike Hezbollah Positions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Israeli Air force (IAF) jet
fighters struck Tuesday morning several Hezbollah (Party of God)
positions in south Lebanon in its fight against "terrorism," an
IAF announcement said.
</P>
<P>
Two IAF jet fighters launched their air raids on the Hezbollah
positions around the Soujud area in the northeast of the Israeli
self-proclaimed security zone in south Lebanon and all fighters
returned to their air base safely, the announcement said.
</P>
<P>
The fighters fired eight rockets and all hit the targets
correctly, it added.
</P>
<P>
Since the beginning of this year, the IAF jet fighters have
constantly been conducting air raids on Hezbollah positions in
the security zone due to the intensified armed conflicts between
Israeli Defense Force (IDF) and Lebanese resistance groups such as
Hezbollah.
</P>
<P>
Last Friday, four IAF paratroopers were lightly wounded when
they helped repulse an attack by Hezbollah gunmen on the South
Lebanese Army's Ghazlan outpost in the northeastern sector of the
security zone.
</P>
<P>
At least three of the Hezbollah attackers were killed by IDF
soliders during the Friday encounter, including one who was shot
while trying to raise Hezbollah's flag on the outpost.
</P>
<P>
Last Thursday, three IDF soldiers, two from the Givati Brigade
and the other from the intelligence corps, were killed when a
mortar round exploded directly outside their observation post at
the Karkum position in the western sector of the security zone.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli security zone in south Lebanon was carved out in
1985 to protect its northern towns from guerrilla attacks.
</P>
<P>
Facing the tense military situation in south Lebanon, Israeli
Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu offered on Sunday to pullout
the IDF troops if the Lebanese government provides the requisite
security backup under the U.N. Security Council Resolution 425.
</P>
<P>
But his proposal has reportedly been rejected by the Lebanese
side.
</P>
<P>
The Security Council Resolution 425 was adopted in 1978,
which calls on Israel to withdraw its troops from south Lebanon
unconditionally. 
</P>
</TEXT>
