<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rita Fan: "One Country, Two Systems" Successful in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- What happened in Hong Kong in the
past eight months proves successful the Chinese government's
concepts of "one country, two systems", and "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong" with a high-degree autonomy.
</P>
<P>
Rita Fan Hsu Lai-tai, a deputy from Hong Kong to the First
Session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), China's new
legislature which opens Thursday, made these remarks here today.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time in history that Hong Kong has sent a
separate 35-member delegation to the annual session of the NPC.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong has run its administrative, legislative and judicial
affairs quite smoothly, maintained social stability and steady
economic growth, and withheld the impact of the financial crisis
in Southeast Asia since China resumed the exercise of sovereignty
over it on July 1 last year, according to Rita Fan, also president
of the Provisional Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (SAR).
</P>
<P>
"The prospects for Hong Kong remain quite rosy," she said.
"Hong Kong has set an excellent example for Macao's return to the
motherland next year and the complete accomplishment of the
country's future peaceful reunification."
</P>
<P>
She noted that Hong Kong SAR has, over the past eight months,
preserved its original social, economic systems, way of life and
basic laws, with no interference by the central government in its
internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, she acknowledged, the central government has rendered
support to Hong Kong in an all-out way, especially during the
financial crisis in the Southeast Asia.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong needs the cooperation and support of the interior
areas to maintain its current status as an international finance,
trade and shipping center and be even more competitive in the
global economy," she added.
</P>
<P>
She pointed to the fact that while Hong Kong has preserved and
further developed its capitalist system and free economy, the
interior areas are effecting an economic shift toward the market
economy under the socialist system.
</P>
<P>
"We should make every effort to retain the characteristics of
both systems, and share our useful experience," she said.
</P>
<P>
She went on to say that it is a rare opportunity for her to be
elected to the NPC and come for the legislature's annual session.
</P>
<P>
"I hope I can have a better understanding of the reforms and
development in the interior areas and make new friends during the
session. Upon my return, I will introduce the session and other
latest developments in the interior to the public," Rita Fan said.
</P>
</TEXT>
