The rise came after a slight drop in January when the reserves
fell to 27.9 billion Rand (5.66 billion dollars) from the 28.5
billion Rand (5.78 billion dollars) at the end of December, 1997.
</P>
<P>
The bank said utilization of foreign credit lines at the end
of February amounted to 9.1 billion Rand (1.85 billion dollars)
against 9.4 billion Rand (1.91 billion dollars) in January.
</P>
