<HEADLINE> Southwestern Province Holds Anti-Drug Exhibition </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- An exhibition marking the
achievements of Yunnan Province's anti-drug campaign opened today
in Kunming, the provincial capital.
</P>
<P>
Sponsored by the Publicity Department of the Yunnan Provincial
Committee of the Communist Party of China and the Anti-Narcotics
Committee of Yunnan Province, the four-part exhibition includes
1,000 pictures and objects selected across the province.
</P>
<P>
Advanced techniques such as multi-media and projection have
been used for the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
Organizers say the purpose of the exhibition is to show the
audience the causes and harmful effects of drugs, and measures and
efforts taken by the province as well as their achievements.
</P>
<P>
Yunnan, on the main route for drug-trafficking to China and
also on the frontline of China's anti-drug efforts, started the
campaign in 1982. The province has cracked more than 50,000 drug
cases, and confiscated 70 tons of drugs during the last 16 years.
</P>
