<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0095 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) is the Chinese people's patriotic
united front organization, a key institution of multi-party
cooperation and political consultations under the leadership of
the Communist Party of China (CPC), and a major form to promote
socialist democracy in China's political life.
</P>
<P>
After the victory of the war of resistance against Japanese
Aggression in 1945, the CPC and the Kuomintang decided during
their negotiations in Chongqing to convene a political
consultative conference and organize a new government.
</P>
<P>
The conference was convened on January 10, 1946, and attended
by representatives of the Kuomintang, the CPC, the Democratic
League, the Youth Party and noted figures. In November the same
year, the Kuomintang unilaterally proclaimed the convention of a
"National Assembly" in violation of the resolution of the
political consultative conference.
</P>
<P>
The first plenary session of the CPPCC National Committee was
held in Beijing in September 1949, exercising the functions of the
supreme state bodies on behalf of the state.
</P>
<P>
The session adopted a "Common Program of the Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference" which bore the nature of a
temporary constitution, proclaiming the founding of the People's
Republic of China (PRC), electing the committee of the Central
People's Government of the PRC with Mao Zedong as its chairman,
and electing the First National Committee of the CPPCC. It also
designated the Chinese capital, national flag and national anthem,
and the way of recording the years.
</P>
<P>
In September 1954, the National People's Congress, the supreme
institution of state power in China, was set up and the CPPCC then
ceased to function on the NPC's behalf. But it continued to exist
as China's patriotic united front organization with broadest
representation and play a vital role in the country's political,
economic, cultural and social affairs and diplomatic exchanges.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0096 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At present, the CPPCC consists of representatives of the CPC
and eight non-Communist parties, people without party affiliation,
people's organizations, and representatives from ethnic minorities
and from all social strata. In addition, there are compatriots
from the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), Macao and
Taiwan, returned overseas Chinese, and specially invited people.
</P>
<P>
The main functions of the CPPCC are political consultation,
democratic supervision and the participation in and deliberation
of state affairs.
</P>
<P>
Political consultation means conferring on major policies of
central and local governments, key policy decisions concerning the
country's political, economic, cultural and social affairs before
the decisions are made, or main issues involved in the process
of carrying them out.
</P>
<P>
Democratic supervision means supervising, by the means of
offering suggestion and criticism over the implementation of the
China's Constitution, relevant laws, regulations and major
policies, over the work of state organs and their functionaries.
</P>
<P>
The participation in and deliberation of state affairs means to
organize various parties, organizations, people from various
ethnic groups and social sectors to take part in the country's
political, economic, cultural and social life in diversified
forms.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC has the National Committee and local committees, with
a five-year tenure for committee members. A plenary session is
held annually.
</P>
<P>
So far, the CPPCC has had Nine National Committees. Mao Zedong,
Zhou Enlai, Deng Xiaoping, Deng Yingchao, Li Xiannian and Li
Ruihuan have served successively as chairmen of the CPPCC National
Committees.
</P>
<P>
The present First Session of the Ninth CPPCC National
Committee, with a total membership of 2,196, opened in Beijing
today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> International Symposium for Preventing Blindness Begins </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government will
greatly enhance cooperation with international health
organizations for preventing blindness, an official said today.
</P>
<P>
Health authorities will focus on cataract surgery in the next
few years, said Ministry of Health official Liu Keling at an
international symposium on preventing blindness which started
today.
</P>
<P>
Some 1.75 million cataract operations were performed between
1988 and 1996, Liu said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Chinese ophthalmologists are trying to lower the
percentage of the blind among the country's population.
</P>
<P>
The three-day symposium will focus on international medical
exchanges and cooperation. Officials from the World Health
Organization, delegates from non-governmental groups and health
officials, experts and scholars from 14 countries and regions are
attending the symposium.
</P>
<P>
China started its blindness prevention program about 40 years
ago, underscoring the prevention and treatment of trachoma, a
chronic eye infection.
</P>
<P>
Foreign officials also expressed a desire for further medical
cooperation with China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
