<HEADLINE> China Publishes Economic Research Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The new book entitled Reform of
State-owned Enterprises in Transition to a Market Economy was
published today in Beijing by People's University.
</P>
<P>
The book provides a comprehensive analysis of the current
status of China's state-owned enterprises, including the
management reform of state assets, mergers and property transfers,
technological advancements, reemployment, and the nation's social
security system.
</P>
<P>
The work also introduces proposals for the further reform of
state-owned enterprises and predicts basic trends in China's
economic systems reform from the standpoint of the said
enterprises.  
</P>
