<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poll: Hun Sen Likely to Win July Elections </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PHNOM PENH, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Cambodia's Second Prime
Minister Hun Sen is likely to win the July national elections,
according to an opinion poll released on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The poll, conducted by the private French Institute for
Statistics, Opinion Polls and Research on Cambodia, showed that
16.6 percent of the 1,875 respondents said they supported Hun Sen.
</P>
<P>
Of those questioned, 13.4 percent said they backed former First
Prime Minister Prince Norodom Ranariddh and 7.8 percent said they
supported former finance minister Sam Rainsy.
</P>
<P>
Of those respondents in the February 26-28 poll, 76.9 percent
said they wanted Ranariddh -- now in exile abroad -- to come back
to run in the July elections while 3.7 percent said they did not
want him to return and 19.4 percent were undecided.
</P>
<P>
And at least 95.4 percent of the people questioned said they
wanted a nationwide ceasefire.
</P>
<P>
Of the 1,875 respondents, 613 were in Phnom Penh and 1,262 in
Kompong Spue and Kompong Chnang provinces. Some 60 percent of the
people declined to answer when asked which leader they backed.
</P>
</TEXT>
