<HEADLINE> Mini Laser Discman Popular in Macao </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Mini laser products like
mini-discman (MD) have increasingly edged walkman to become the
latest fashion in Macao, the Macao Daily News reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Sales of these items rose considerably last year as the prices
dropped to between 500 patacas (about 62.5 US dollars) and 2,000
patacas (about 250 US dollars), down about 20 percent to 50
percent from the previous year.
</P>
<P>
The report said that mini laser disc-player first arrived at
Macao market in 1996, but was left in the cold due to its high
price.
</P>
<P>
However, many Macao hi-fi fans began to accept the sound of MD
last year, when an overall price drop appeared. The report said
sales rose but gave no figures.
</P>
<P>
MD dealers in Macao predict that laser audio systems will
continue to dominate Macao's audio market in the coming two years,
and that the MD market, in particular, will get a boost as the
price drops further.  
</P>
</TEXT>
