<HEADLINE> South China City Developing Tourism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Guilin city in south China's
Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region known for its scenic mountains
and rivers, has developed facilities in recent years to boost the
growth of its tourism industry.
</P>
<P>
It has received at least 7 million tourists from 130 countries
and regions and 100 million Chinese tourists over the past 20
years.
</P>
<P>
The city now has 29 hotels in various categories, with
over 14,000 beds and nearly 20,000 employees. The new Liangjiang
International Airport handles ten million passengers annually.
</P>
<P>
The city has also developed new tourism programs like the Lijiang
River trip at night, cave adventures and photography tours. Its
tourism zones have grown to 200 and it has 120 tourist
routes to other cities.
</P>
<P>
It has expanded tourist markets to Japan and has begun to
attract tourists from the Republic of Korea and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
 
