<HEADLINE> Neo-Nazi, Racist Crimes Up in German Army </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Neo-Nazi and racist crimes in
Germany's armed forces increased to 177 cases involving 229
soliders last year, a parliamentary report said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
In comparison, 44 such cases were registered in 1996, said the
report released by Claire Marienfeld, the German parliament's
armed forces commissioner.
</P>
<P>
The neo-Nazi incidents in the 340,000-strong German armed
forces ranged from attacks on foreigners to drunken parties at
which soldiers gave the stiff-armed Hitler salute.
</P>
<P>
The report said the situation in the military, known as the
Bundeswehr in German, was a reflection of the growing trend to use
violence and the rise in far-right offenses in society. 
</P>
