<HEADLINE> Ye Xuanping Summarizes CPPCC Work (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) --Ye Xuanping, vice-chairman of the
Eighth National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), said the country's top advisory
body has made outstanding achievements in the last five years.
</P>
<P>
In his speech delivered at the opening session of the First
Session of the Ninth CPPCC National Committee on behalf of the
Standing Committee of the Eighth CPPCC National Committee, Ye said
the country's top advisory body has promoted the standardization
and institutionalization of political consultation, democratic
supervision and participation in the deliberation and
administration of state affairs and pushed forward its work
actively, steadily and in an orderly way.
</P>
<P>
"We have subordinated ourselves to and served overall national
undertakings and have made important contributions to reform,
opening to the outside world, the modernization drive and a
peaceful reunification of the motherland," Ye said.
</P>
<P>
The Eighth National Committee of the CPPCC adhered to basic
policy guidelines for the primary stage of socialism, earnestly
studied Deng Xiaoping's teachings with regard to CPPCC in a new
historical period, carried out policy decisions and directives
made by the CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core
regarding CPPCC-related work, he said.
</P>
<P>
It has also followed and improved multi-party co-operation and
political consultation system under the leadership of the
Communist Party of China, he said.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC has effectively performed its functions and made
itself a major channel through which the CPC can unite people of
all circles and consult with them on state affairs.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0118 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ye Xuanping Summarizes CPPCC Work (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ye said the CPC Central Committee requires that, before central
or local governments formulate major policies or make decisions on
major issues in political, economic, cultural and other fields,
they must consult with the CPPCC.
</P>
<P>
He said the Eighth National Committee of the CPPCC convened
meetings and consultative forums on all major state affairs,
providing broad-based political support for major national
undertakings.
</P>
<P>
Members of the CPPCC National Committee, he said, raised
proposals and suggestions on draft annual government work reports,
the establishment of a socialist market economy, the formulation
of plans for national economic and social development and the
promotion of socialist cultural and ethical progress, he said.
</P>
<P>
"On the basis of consultations and discussions, we raised
comments and suggestions and arranged our work in accordance with
the realities of the CPPCC," he said.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, he said, members of the CPPCC National
Committee held consultative seminars with officials of the central
authorities and departments on a wide range of issues including
the national economy, the fight against corruption, promotion of a
honest government, agricultural development, farmland protection,
development of education and public security.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, while focusing on the country's
central task and major issues of common concern, the CPPCC
National Committee organized its members for special
investigations and inspection tours, he said.
</P>
<P>
Members produced a total of 187 investigative reports and
proposals, 80 inspection reports, nearly 2,000 written speeches
and over 11,700 motions, he said.
</P>
<P>
The proposals, including those on tightening macroeconomic
controls and curbing inflation, had important reference value
for the central authorities in decision making, he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0119 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ye Xuanping Summarizes CPPCC Work (3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The CPPCC National Committee has expanded its functions. The
Second Session of the Eighth National Committee of the CPPCC
adopted a revised Constitution of the CPPCC. According to the
revised Constitution, the CPPCC has the new function of
"participating in the deliberation and administration of state
affairs" in addition to that of "political consultation and
democratic supervision."
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC National Committee also regarded the reporting of
social conditions and popular feelings as one of its essential and
vital functions, he said. It opened up new sources of information,
launched its own information journal, set up offices for the
collection of information and established an information network,
he said.
</P>
<P>
"All these have opened up new channels for informing the
central authorities of social conditions and popular feelings and
offered a wider arena in which our members can participate in the
deliberation and administration of state affairs," he said.
</P>
<P>
Members of the CPPCC National Committee, local CPPCC
committees, the central committees of democratic parties and the
All-China Federation of Industry and Commerce provided over 8,000
pieces of information on social conditions and popular feelings
and forwarded over 59,900 letters to the central leadership over
the past five years.
</P>
<P>
The country's top advisory body has also made contributions
to promoting unity and stability and to the reunification of the
motherland, he said.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with unified plans of the Chinese government, the
Eighth National Committee of the CPPCC cooperated with relevant
departments in ensuring the return of Hong Kong and Macao to the
motherland.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the CPPCC expanded and strengthened
contacts and exchanges with people of all walks of life in Hong
Kong, compatriots in Macao and Taiwan and Chinese residing
abroad.
</P>
<P>
The CPPCC publicized and adhered to the principled stand that
there is only one China in the world. It is opposed to splittism,
"independence of Taiwan," attempts to create "two Chinas" or "one
China, one Taiwan." And it promoted economic and cultural
exchanges and cooperation between the two sides of the Taiwan
Strait.
</P>
<P>
It has also done a great deal to accelerate the establishment
of direct postal, air and shipping services and trade between the
two sides and for the complete reunification of the motherland, he
said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
