<HEADLINE> Chinese Company Wins Bidding on Sudanese Pipeline Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China's leading oil company, the
China National Petroleum Corporation, has won the international
bidding for a large pipeline project in Sudan, according to
International Business Daily.
</P>
<P>
The 1,610-km pipeline is expected to cost 600 million US dollars
and is Sudan's largest ever to be opened for international
bidding, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The first phase of the three-phase project will start later
this year and the whole project is expected to be completed by
1999.
</P>
<P>
Several other oil companies have joined China National in
providing the oil pipes for the project. 
</P>
</TEXT>
