<HEADLINE> Ye Xuanping Summarizes CPPCC Work (4) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Ye told the session that the CPPCC made friendly contacts with
other countries within the framework of China's general foreign
policy and in a multi-level manner.
</P>
<P>
During its term, the CPPCC Eighth National Committee sent 52
delegations or groups to 56 countries and invited and received 55
delegations or groups from 34 countries. By the end of 1997, the
CPPCC had established contacts with 98 institutions in 68
countries and four international organizations and conducted
friendly exchanges with them.
</P>
<P>
Turning to the CPPCC Ninth National Committee, he said
the grand program formulated at the 15th National Congress of the
CPC has provided new opportunities for the development of the
CPPCC and set a higher demand on the CPPCC as well, he said.
</P>
<P>
"The CPPCC should consolidate and develop a broad patriotic
united front and make progress through exploration and
experimentation," he said.
</P>
<P>
"It should focus on tasks set by the 15th National Congress of
the CPC, take a new approach in its work and advance the cause of
CPPCC to the 21st century in an all-round way," Ye said.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the Eighth National Committee of the CPPCC, Ye
Xuanping proposed that members of the Ninth National Committee
of the CPPCC study Deng Xiaoping Theory hard, participate in the
deliberation and administration of state affairs, further
standardize and institutionalize the performance of CPPCC
functions, make friends in all circles to promote the
reunification of the motherland, continue to expand friendly
exchanges with other countries and work for CPPCC's
self-improvement. 
</P>
