<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Press Hails Opening of Chinese Conferences </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The people of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region (SAR) can, through their
participation in the National People's Congress (NPC) and the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), play a
unique role in the handling of state affairs, a Hong Kong
newspaper said in an editorial Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The First Session of the Ninth National Committee of the CPPCC
opens in Beijing on Tuesday while the First Session of the Ninth
National Committee of the NPC opens in the Chinese capital on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong Commercial Daily said in its editorial that the
two conferences are of far-reaching significance as the deputies
are to elect a new state leadership who will lead the country into
the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
For the people of the SAR, the editorial said, the two
conferences are unique as this is the first time such conferences
are to be held since Hong Kong's reunification with the motherland
last July. The fact that Hong Kong deputies had formed their
first ever independent delegations for the conferences,
demonstrated the change of Hong Kong's historical status.
</P>
<P>
Some deputies said that they had an entirely new feeling that a
new historical era has come and that they are going to handle the
state affairs as masters of their own country.
</P>
<P>
It also showed the central government has attached great
importance to the SAR people's participation and their role in
handling the country's major issues, the editorial pointed out.
</P>
<P>
Another daily newspaper Ta Kung Pao said in an editorial on
Tuesday that the opening of the conferences is a primary matter in
the political life of the Chinese people and it is an
unprecedented matter of historical significance to the SAR.
</P>
<P>
The participation in the conferences by the deputies of the SAR
as the citizens of the People's Republic of China is a most
important and fundamental change of the political status of the
Hong Kong people since the handover and it is a major milestone to
mark the end of the British rule, it added.
</P>
<P>
An article carried by Wen Wei Po, a daily newspaper, said
Tuesday that as the SAR deputies are facing a solemn and hard
task in the next five years, it is only natural that high
expectations are placed on them.
</P>
<P>
The conferences are of primary importance as they are to form a
new political structure with serving terms right into the next
century, and main topics such as election of a new leadership,
re-employment, guarding against financial crisis and fighting
against corruption, will all be in the limelight, the article
said.
</P>
<P>
Both Hong Kong and China's inland are confronted with new
opportunities and challenges when approaching to the new century,
the article said, adding that SAR's deputies are expected to be
competent for their historical tasks and duties, and they will
work hard to build a stronger and more vigorous China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
