<HEADLINE> Dhaka to Get Food Aid From WFP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The World Food Program (WFP) will
provide 183,000 tons of grains to Bangladesh for sustainable food
security and poverty alleviation programs, the BSS national news
agency said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Of the grains, about 155,550 tons or 85 percent will be used
for a rural development project and allocated to areas with high
and moderate food insecurity.
</P>
<P>
The rural development project is expected to generate
employment for half a million people including 175,000 women and
benefit about three million rural poor, BSS said.
</P>
<P>
Part of the food aid will be used for implementing water
development projects under Bangladesh Water Development Board
(BWDB).
</P>
<P>
The BWDB projects, including the rehabilitation and maintenance
of 239 flood-control embankments and drainage canals and
irrigation schemes, will employ some 200,000 rural people and
benefit some 8 million people, BSS added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
