<HEADLINE> China Hails Security Council Passage of U.N.-Iraq Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China today hailed the
U.N. Security Council's unanimous passage of a resolution which
examined and approved the memorandum of understanding signed
between the United Nations and Iraq last week.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao made the remarks
here at a regular news briefing.
</P>
<P>
The resolution will lay the foundation to fairly and justly
solve the Iraqi weapons-inspection issue thoroughly in a peaceful
way, he said.
</P>
<P>
China considers that the pressing matter of the moment is to
implement the memorandum of understanding as soon as possible, in
case of recurrence of the crisis, he said.
</P>
<P>
China hopes Iraq observes its obligations conscientiously, he
said, adding that China consistently has upheld solving
international disputes by peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the current resolution in no way means that
the U.N. Security Council will automatically authorize any state
to use force against Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Only the Security Council can discuss and determine whether
Iraq violates the memorandum of understanding and, if so, what
action can be taken, he added.  
</P>
