<HEADLINE> Chinese Spokesman Comments on Cambodian Situation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China supports all efforts that
are conducive to stability and national unity in Cambodia, China's
Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao said at a regular news
conference here today.
</P>
<P>
Asked to comment on the recent situation in Cambodia, Zhu said
China, a friendly neighbor to Cambodia, has been following the
situation in Cambodia closely.
</P>
<P>
He said China hopes to see the situation in Cambodia will
stabilize soon, the general election will be held as scheduled in
which all lawful political parties in the country can participate
freely and fairly, and the Cambodian people can fully exercise
their rights and make independent decisions on the affairs of
their nation.
</P>
<P>
China has noticed that some countries have offered proposals on
the Cambodia issue, he said.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Cambodia is a sovereign state, and its
internal problems should, in the final analysis, be resolved by
all the parties concerned in Cambodia through consultation.
</P>
<P>
China sincerely hopes that, under the leadership of King
Norodom Sihanouk and in the spirit of national reconciliation,
these parties will properly address their partisan political
differences and work together for the stability and development of
the nation, he said.
</P>
<P>
China also hopes for a peaceful, tranquil, united, and
progressive Cambodia in the 21st century to make a positive
contribution to the peace, stability and development of this
region, Zhu said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
