<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0150 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 200 World Companies to Attend Macao Trade Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Joao Domingos, president of the Macao Trade and Investment
Promotion Institute, which co-sponsored the fair, said at a press
conference here on Tuesday that businessmen from Hong Kong, Japan,
the Philippines, Portugal, Mozambique, the Republic of Korea,
Spain, Taiwan and the United States as well as Macao will attend
the fair.
</P>
<P>
The U.S., Japan and Mozambique will for the first time attend
the fair which will be held between April 1 and 5. Domingos said
that some Australian companies are also pondering to attend the
annual event.
</P>
<P>
Aiming to enhance cooperation, trade exchange and promote
investment between Macao, China's inland and other countries and
regions, the fair will help promote Macao's international image
and status, said the president.
</P>
<P>
A total of 90,000 people are expected to visit the fair,
outnumbering that of last year. Trade and investment volume are
estimated to arrive at last year's level of about 120 million
patacas (about 15 million U.S. dollars). The volume for 1996 was
70 million patacas (about 8.75 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
So far, 29 companies from China's inland have applied to come,
and the number of Macao participants is estimated at 50. There
will be 10 from Portugal. The deadline for application is March
15.
</P>
<P>
Most of the stalls will show garments and foodstuff, Domingos
said. The fair will also present products of such industries as
tourism, sound and video systems, fire detection systems, toys,
transport, distribution and logistics, furniture, houseware and
decoration, textile and garment machinery, maintenance and civil
engineering, office automation, computers, among others. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
