<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Environment Information Market Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- An information market for
environmental protection has been established in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Jointly run by the Shanghai Municipal Department of Environment
Protection and the government of Hongkou District, the information
market has just completed its first phase of construction.
</P>
<P>
Occupying 1,800 square meters, the market aims to expedite
information exchanges for personnel engaged in environmental
protection services.
</P>
<P>
Technology consultation, designs for environmental protection
projects, scientific and technological research for the projects,
and investment programs about environmental protection are
expected to be managed on the market.
</P>
<P>
According to the administrative office of the market, a
computer network with eight data banks will be installed for the
market so that the people can get access to advanced technology at
home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
An official said that the second-phase construction for the
market is to construct a building. Up to now, more than 100
institutions in 16 provinces and regions have signed for future
services in the building.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
