<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> NPC Session to Underline Democratic, Efficient Work Style </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The First Session of the Ninth
National People's Congress (NPC) due on Thursday, which marks the
beginning of the five-year term of office for China's new
legislature, will be more democratic, efficient and pragmatic than
any previous NPC session.
</P>
<P>
According to a source involved in the session's preparatory
work, deputies from the grassroots units will have a host of
occasions to air their views, and all lawmakers are encouraged to
tell true and practical words instead of empty remarks, in their
panel discussions.
</P>
<P>
"We hope that the deputies will report on the people's true
desires and complaints and offer useful advices for the
development of their country," he said.
</P>
<P>
"Speeches that resemble work reports are not welcome," said the
official, who declined to offer his own name.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, well-informed sources said, all deputies are urged to
concentrate their mind on the conference, with particular
attention attached to the agenda of the session, which is
scheduled to last till March 19.
</P>
<P>
During the session, all local delegations are forbidden to pay
visits to any central government departments to seek their
approval or assistance for economic projects in their respective
areas, or to host dinners to entertain each other or officials
from ministries and commissions under the State Council.
</P>
<P>
The annual session of the NPC is taken as a major event in the
country's political life, and the Chinese lawmakers have, over
recent years, witnessed marked improvement in the mood in which
major state issues are discussed or deliberated, the official
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
