<HEADLINE> Chinese Telecoms Company Has High Goals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China Unicom, based in Beijing,
has planned to increase the number of its digital mobile phone
customers by 750,000 this year, bringing the total to 1.25 million
in 86 cities.
</P>
<P>
The company has also planned to complete the laying of a
10,000-kilometer optical fiber cable and construction of
switchboards in 25 major Chinese cities this year.
</P>
<P>
The company's general manager, Li Huifen, says that this year
the company wants to establish a mobile phone network for the
Yangtze and Pearl river deltas, the Bohai Bay area, and the
capitals of all provinces and autonomous regions, and developed
cities.
</P>
<P>
China Unicom was founded in 1994 and is China's second largest
basic telecoms company. Its digital mobile phone network covers 80
cities with a capacity of 1.2 million lines and has more than
500,000 customers. It has long-distance and urban telephone
services and satellite transmission. 
</P>
