<HEADLINE> China Eastern Air Group Receives Delivery of A320 Jetliner </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China Eastern Air Group recently
took delivery of its first single-aisle Airbus A320 jetliner at
Lukou Airport in Nanjing, the capital of east China's Jiangsu
Province.
</P>
<P>
The A320 is the first of 10 being leased from General Electric
Capital Aviation Services of the United States. The first five
A320s, to be delivered this year, will be operated by China
Eastern Jiangsu Airlines Ltd., a joint venture between China
Eastern and the Jiangsu provincial government. The remaining five
aircraft will be handed over to China Eastern Jiangxi branch in
Nanchang by 2000.
</P>
<P>
China Eastern has opted for a 158-seat cabin configuration for
the A320s including eight in first class and 150 in economy class.
</P>
<P>
The A320 has a wider cabin, larger under-floor compartment, and
more satisfactory passenger appeal compared with other
single-aisle aircraft, officials said.
</P>
<P>
China Eastern Air Group became the first operator of Airbus
jetliners in China in 1985. It currently operates 10 A300-600R and
five A340-300 aircraft.  
</P>
</TEXT>
