<HEADLINE> Over 100,000 Cars Stolen in U.S. in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, March 2 (Xinhua) -- More than 100,000 cars were
stolen last year in the United States and Japan-made cars were the
most stolen ones, a U.S. agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
"This year's study reflects the growing popularity of foreign
cars not only among consumers but also among car thieves," said
Jack Rozint, senior vice president of Chicago-based CCC
Information Services Inc., adding that 1989 Toyota Camry led the
list of 1997's most stolen cars in the country.
</P>
<P>
Thefts accounted for most of the nation's vehicle insurance
claims, added CCC Information Services Inc., which tracks
reports on auto thefts for the insurance industry. 
</P>
