<HEADLINE> First Session of CPPCC Ninth National Committee Opens (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The First Session of the Ninth
National Committee of the Chinese People's Political Consultative
Conference (CPPCC) opened here this afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The session has drawn world attention because the leadership of
the CPPCC National Committee, the body of most extensive patriotic
united front in China, will be elected.
</P>
<P>
At 3:00 p.m., Li Ruihuan, an executive chairman of the
session's presidium who presides over the meetings of the
presidium's executive chairmen, declared the session open, with
the band playing the tune of the resonant national anthem.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Communist Party and state leading officials, including
Jiang Zemin, Li Peng, Qiao Shi, Zhu Rongji, Liu Huaqing, Hu
Jintao, Wei Jianxing, Li Lanqing and Rong Yiren, attended the
opening ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The Ninth CPPCC National Committee has 2,196 members, the most
numerous compared with any previous national committees,
demonstrating this united front organization has the broadest
representation.
</P>
<P>
Ye Xuanping, vice-chairman of the CPPCC Eighth National
Committee, delivered a report on the work of the Standing
Committee of the Eighth CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
He said the people's consultative work constitutes an
important component part of the great cause of building
socialist with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
Over the past five years, he noted, the Eighth National
Committee of the CPPCC has adhered to multi-party cooperation and
political consultations under the leadership of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) and worked hard to further improve them, so
as to ensure that the CPPCC acts as an important channel for the
CPC to unite the people of various sectors in conferring on state
issues and coordinating relations.
</P>
<P>
Ye Xuanping reviewed the work of the Eighth CPPCC National
Committee on conducting political consultations, performing its
functions, and promoting unity, exchanges with other countries,
work in localities and self-improvement.
</P>
</TEXT>
