<HEADLINE> 23 Filipinos Downed by Food Poisoning </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Some 23 tribesmen in Cotabato
province, southern Philippines, suffered food poisoning after they
ate a wild crop due to food scarcity caused by the El Nino
phenomenon.
</P>
<P>
The Philippine News Agency reported on Tuesday that the
tribesmen have resorted to eating wild yam since February 12 owing
to the lack of food.
</P>
<P>
Marlow Nial, chief of the Regional Emergency Surveillance Unit
in Central Mindanao, said that the victims experienced severe
headache, stomach ache, diarrhea and sagging of eyelids as a
result of the toxic substance present in the yam.
</P>
<P>
The victims are now being treated by doctors working with the
Regional Emergency Surveillance Unit. 
