<HEADLINE> Old Photos Provide New Images </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- An "Old Photos" program
broadcast by Hunan Provincial Economic Television Station makes
old photos come alive to tell moving stories unknown to most
people.
</P>
<P>
An exhibition of 100-years-old photos in Kunming, capital of
southwest China's Yunnan Province, has become a hot topic among
local residents.
</P>
<P>
Collections of old photos and albums are taking prominent
positions in China's book stores, big or small.
</P>
<P>
Shandong Pictorial Publishing House pulled open the curtains of
this event by publishing a magazine titled "Old Photos" in 1996.
</P>
<P>
To date, 240,000 copies of the magazine have been sold.
</P>
<P>
Many of the photos included in the magazine reflect images of
noted people, the lives of older generations and their personal
experience in different historical periods.
</P>
<P>
Sociologists believe this is a new way for people to study
history in addition to writing articles.
</P>
<P>
Some readers, however, said that they love to see the old
photos because they contain much information.  
</P>
