<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> U.S. Research Team Finds Another Alzheimer's Link in Genes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, March 2 (Xinhua) -- A team of U.S. researchers has
found a gene that may increase the risk of Alzheimer's disease
fourfold, acorrding to a report in the March issue of Nature
Genetics magazine.
</P>
<P>
The gene is linked to the sporadic form of Alzheimer's, which
generally appears in individuals who lack a family history of the
disorder. Now researchers at the University of Pittsburgh have
discovered a so-called susceptbility gene.
</P>
<P>
The report said that those with the gene won't necessarily
develop Alzheimer's, but their risk is higher. It carries the
blueprint for an enzyme involved in the metabolism of beta-amyloid
protein, the substance that destroys brain cells in Alzheimer's
patients.
</P>
<P>
The Pittsburgh team said that everybody has this enzyme, but
people with Alzheimer's appear to have an over representation of
it. The gene comes in an "A" form and a "G" form. Everybody
inherits two copies of the gene. The study suggests an effect only
when both copies are the "G" form.
</P>
<P>
An estimated four million people in the United States are
afflicted of Alzheimer's, a neurological disorder which destroys
memory and judgement.
</P>
<P>
Scientists in recent years also have identified genes on
chromosomes 1,14 and 21, linking them to the early onset of
Alzheimer's disease. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0188 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Making Progress in Publicizing ISO9000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China has improved its quality
control of export-oriented enterprises and foreign trade by
adopting the internationally accepted ISO9000 standard series.
</P>
<P>
By the end of 1997, 1,001 export-oriented enterprises have been
granted certificates for having met ISO9000 quality control
standards, according to statistics from the State Administration
for the Inspection of Import and Export Commodities.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that ISO9000 quality control standards were worked
out by the International Standardization Organization (ISO) in
1987 in light of modern management theories.
</P>
<P>
The ISO9000 quality standard certificate has been considered a
guarantee of good product quality, trustworthiness and modern
management, and a "passport" for businesses to compete in the
international market.
</P>
<P>
To improve the competitiveness of Chinese-made products in
world markets, China has established an ISO9000 working committee
to popularize the quality system in export-oriented companies.
</P>
<P>
The ISO9000 quality standard certificate has helped state-owned
enterprises transform their management mechanism, said officials
from the administration.
</P>
<P>
The Kunming Cable Company in southwest China's Yunnan Province,
one of the country's 26 key cable enterprises, earned 3.6 million
U.S. dollars of foreign exchange in 1997 because of the ISO9000
quality certificate it gained in 1995.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, export-oriented enterprises have raised their
credibility and competitiveness in the international market after
receiving ISO9000 certificates, said the officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
