<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0194 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Backgrounder: Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference Sessions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The First Session of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) was held in
Beijing between September 21 and 30, 1949, exercising the
functions of China's highest organ of state power. It was attended
by 662 representatives from all walks of life.
</P>
<P>
The first CPPCC session adopted "Common Program of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference," proclaimed the
founding of the People's Republic of China and elected a Committee
of the Central People's Government with Mao Zedong as its
chairman. It also decided the national flag and national anthem,
elected the First National Committee of the CPPCC which was
composed of 180 members, and set October 1st as the National Day.
The CPPCC First National Committee held four sessions.
</P>
<P>
The First Session of the Second National Committee of the CPPCC
was held in Beijing in December 1954 with 559 participants.
</P>
<P>
According to "Constitution of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference" adopted at the session, the CPPCC would
no longer exercise the power of the National People's Congress
(NPC) owing to the convention of the NPC First Session. But the
CPPCC would continue to exist as an organization of people's
democratic united front work. The session elected Mao Zedong as
honorary chairman of the Second CPPCC National Committee and Zhou
Enlai as its chairman. The Second CPPCC National Committee had
three sessions.
</P>
<P>
The First Session of the Third CPPCC National Committee was
held in April, 1959 in Beijing, which was attended by 1,071
members. Starting from this session, CPPCC national committee members
attended NPC sessions in a non-voting capacity. Mao Zedong and
Zhou Enlai were elected, respectively, honorary chairman and
chairman of the Third CPPCC National Committee, which held four
sessions.
</P>
<P>
The fourth CPPCC National Committee held its first session
between December 1964 and January 1965 in Beijing. It was attended
by 1,199 members. Mao Zedong and Zhou Enlai were once again
elected honorary chairman and chairman of the CPPCC National
Committee. However, it ceased all activities during the "Great
Cultural Revolution" (1966-1976). The Fourth CPPCC National
Committee held only one session.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,988 members attended the First Session of
the Fifth CPPCC National Committee held between February and
March in 1978. Deng Xiaoping was elected chairman of the Fifth
CPPCC National Committee, which had five sessions.
</P>
<P>
The First Session of the Sixth CPPCC National Committee was
held in June, 1983 in Beijing with 2,039 participants. Deng
Yingchao was elected its chairman. The committee had five
sessions.
</P>
<P>
The Seventh CPPCC National Committee held its first session
between March 24 and April 10, 1988 with 2,081 participants. Li
Xiannian was elected its chairman. It had five sessions.
</P>
<P>
The First Session of the Eighth CPPCC National Committee was
held between March 14 and 27, 1993 in Beijing with 2,093
participants. It elected Li Ruihuan its chairman. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0195 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
