<HEADLINE> Turkish Ambassador Arrives in Tehran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Newly-appointed Turkish ambassador
to Iran Sencar Ozsoy arrived here early Tuesday morning, one year
after Ankara and Tehran recalled their ambassadors to the other,
a Turkish source told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The source said that Ozsoy, 56, served as Turkish ambassador
to Argentina before coming here.
</P>
<P>
Local newspaper Iran News reported Tuesday that Iranian
ambassador to Turkey Mohammad Hussein Lavasani would leave here
for Ankara this weekend.
</P>
<P>
In February last year, Iranian ambassador to Turkey Mohammad
Reza Baqeri angered the Turkish government by delivering a
pro-Islamic speech during a demonstration. Ankara ordered Baqeri
to leave the country and Tehran in turn expelled the Turkish
ambassador to Iran.
</P>
<P>
The two countries sent special envoys to each other in order
to repair their relations and they decided to exchange
ambassadors on the sidelines of the 8th summit of the
Organization of the Islamic Conference (OIC) held in Tehran last
December in which Turkish President Suleyman Demirel took part.
</P>
<P>
However, serious differences still remain between Iran and
Turkey, particularly over Turkish military cooperation with Israel
and Turkish military incursion into northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian government strongly opposed Turkish military
cooperation with Israel and repeatedly asked Ankara to reconsider
its decision. Tehran also called on Ankara to respect Iraq's
sovereignty and territorial integrity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
