<HEADLINE> All Ethnic Minorities Have Representatives in NPC (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
She attributed the improvement to the success of China's system
of regional autonomy for ethnic minorities and intensified
protection of women's rights and interests by the Chinese
government.
</P>
<P>
Reports say that women's associations in northwest China's
Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region have helped more than one
million women from various ethnic minorities to master at least one
practical agricultural skill.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruzhong, an NPC deputy representing the Lahu ethnic group in
southwest China's Yunnan Province, said that thanks to the care
and assistance of the government, the 430,000 Lahu people have bid
farewell to their primitive way of life.
</P>
<P>
"We used to move around and hunt in the thick forests. Now We
have settled down, and some of us even own private cars," said Li,
head of the government of the country's sole Lahu autonomous
county.
</P>
<P>
Adili, a Uygur deputy from Xinjiang, received effusive media
coverage as soon as he arrived in Beijing for the NPC session.
</P>
<P>
The 26-year-old tightrope walker last June spent 13.8 minutes
crossing China's longest Yangtze River on a 640.75-meter-long
steel wire stretched 375 meters above the water, breaking the
Guinness World Record set in 1995 by Canadian Jay Cochraine by
nearly 40 minutes.
</P>
<P>
The young man revealed that he has been invited to walk the
tightrope over the Niagara Falls, which have a span of over 1,200
meters, in April this year.
</P>
<P>
"I will prove with my performance that the Chinese can do great
feats," he vowed. 
</P>
