<HEADLINE> China's Telecommunications Company Hopes to Enter World's Top 50 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The East Communications Co. Ltd.,
China's largest state-owned, share-holding wireless
telecommunications manufacturer, expects to become one of the
world's top 50 telecommunications companies by 2000.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Shi Jixing, chairman of the East
Communications, said the company has upgraded its cooperation with
Motorola and Lucent Technologies from technical transfers to joint
investments to further explore the potential of China's mobile
telephone market, which expects to add 35 million subscribers by
2000.
</P>
<P>
So far, two joint ventures have been set up specializing in
CDMA (code diversion multiple access) cellular phones and digital
telecommunications equipment.
</P>
<P>
The company with its headquarters in the city of Hangzhou in
east China's Zhejiang Province, has annual sales of 1.6 million
mobile telephones. At present, one in seven Chinese mobile
telephone subscribers has an East-made Motorola product which
carries the East Communications trademark. 
</P>
</TEXT>
