<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shanghai Stamp Auction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai International
Commodity Auction Company will hold a large auction of Chinese
stamps on March 15 and is expecting to raise more than six million
yuan from the sale.
</P>
<P>
Up for grabs will be 841 items, the most valuable of which is a
block of mint "The Whole Country is Red" stamps, with the margin
still attached. They show a red map of China above joyful
soldiers, workers, and peasants, and were intended for issue
during the Cultural Revolution, on November 24, 1968. Authorities
then decided not to issue them, but post offices in remote areas
got news late and several hundred were sold. They are expected to
bring at least 700,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
Other rare stamps from the period will also be available, like
"The Great Victory of the Cultural Revolution". There are also
several unique stamps from the Republic of China (1912-1949),
which will bring at least 200,000 yuan each, a high price for a
single stamp. There are only a dozen of these stamps available in
the world.
</P>
<P>
The stamps will be on display for three days before the auction
for buyers and stamp collectors to see.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Private Business in East China Province Eyes High-Tech Industries </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Private business in east
China's Zhejiang Province is playing a more forceful role in
developing high-tech products.
</P>
<P>
Zhejiang-based enterprises engaged in high-tech products
development now number 6,400 and employ more than 120,000 people,
68 percent of them being technical professionals. These
firms have earned 10 billion yuan (1.2 billion U.S. dollars) in
annual sales for two consecutive years.
</P>
<P>
Nearly two-thirds of these enterprises are collectively owned,
and an increasing number of the private firms are pursuing
cooperation with their overseas counterparts.
</P>
<P>
The firms are gaining support from local governments and
science institutes to develop patented products and expand their
business scale. Many of them have set up their own research
centers, laboratories and consultation and service departments.
</P>
<P>
A local, privately owned anti-cancer drug producer has acquired
patents both at home and in the United States. Both its annual
output value and sales have exceeded 100 million yuan (12 million
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The Zhejiang Huiqiang Electrical Group, which has total assets
of 50 million yuan, has been the first domestic developer of
digital laser Video Disk (DVD) of an international advanced level
and appraised by the Ministry of Electronics Industry.
</P>
<P>
The Hangzhou Tongpu Electrical Co. has been committed to
producing a series of telecommunications facilities, such as
digital program-controlled switchboards. It has an annual output
value of over 100 million yuan.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
