<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Limits Jobs for Outside Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Municipal Government
plans to restrict outside laborers seeking jobs in the Chinese
capital, city officials said recently.
</P>
<P>
The Labor Bureau will limit outside people to employment in
such posts as finance, insurance, secretarial, accounting and
management.
</P>
<P>
But they can find other 200 kinds of opportunities in commerce,
agriculture, chemical industry and construction, officials said.
</P>
<P>
Businesses in Beijing should first consider employing local
residents, especially those who are unemployed, according to an
announcement made by the bureau.
</P>
<P>
Local jobless workers must account for at least 50 percent of
the new posts created by the service sector this year, the
announcement said.
</P>
<P>
Any business which violates the announcement may face financial
punishment, officials said.
</P>
<P>
The city expects another 200,000 lay-offs this year, officials
estimated.
</P>
<P>
However, some private business runners favor employing outside
job-seekers, who usually accept low wages in the city.  
</P>
</TEXT>
