<HEADLINE> Mongolia Guards Against Grass, Forest Fires </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Mongolian government
Tuesday urged the whole nation to take precautions against grass
and forest fires.
</P>
<P>
In a notice, the State Standing Emergency Commission cautioned
that fires will easily break out in spring due to the dry weather,
and required that materials and human resources be well prepared
to guard against the possibility.
</P>
<P>
It said officials slack on anti-fire work will be held
responsible for any accident as arsonists.
</P>
<P>
The commission also demanded the frontier forces to closely
cooperate with their counterparts in neighboring countries to
prevent cross-border fires.
</P>
<P>
Mongolia has already suffered three grass and forest fires this
year. 
</P>
