<HEADLINE> US Urges Indonesia to Fully Implement Reform Program </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Visiting US special envoy Walter
Mondale said here Tuesday that the best way to restore public
confidence in the Indonesia economy is fully implementing the IMF
(International Monetary Fund) reform program.
</P>
<P>
Talking to newsmen after a 90-minute meeting with Indonesian
President Soeharto at the latter's residence in Central Jakarta,
Mondale said they mainly discussed the recent economic situation
in Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Indonesia and the IMF signed an agreement on January 15 this
year on an IMF-led 43 billion U.S. dollar bailout, and in
exchange, the Indonesian government agreed to carry out economic
and financial reforms to overcome its current monetary crisis.
</P>
<P>
Besides the IMF reforms, Mondale said, they also discussed
further steps necessary to restore economic growth as well as
reestablish market confidence in the future for Indonesia.
</P>
<P>
Mondale, former US vice president under Jimmy Carter, arrived
here on Monday for a two-day visit.
</P>
<P>
The US agreed in October last year to offer 3 billion U.S.
dollars in the IMF-framework to Indonesia. 
</P>
</TEXT>
