<HEADLINE> East China Province Encouraging Technology Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China's Shandong Province plans to
increase technology trade with foreign countries in the coming
years, according to local officials.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Shandong's foreign trade is worth 20 billion US
dollars annually, but technology exports account for only one
percent of that.
</P>
<P>
Under the new plan, the province expects to increase its
technology exports to 3 billion US dollars a year, or 6 percent of
the foreign trade, and technology imports to 15 percent by 2010.
</P>
<P>
In the past, technology exports mostly consisted of equipment
for small power stations, the rubber industry, or paper mills, but
in the future, the province will export hi-tech products. It will
also encourage local companies to work on large industrial
projects overseas in various ways. 
</P>
</TEXT>
