<HEADLINE> Chinese Government Buys Leading Rubber Producer's Stockpile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese government has bought
20,000 tons of rubber from the island province of Hainan to help
remove the huge stockpile of China's leading rubber producer.
</P>
<P>
The State-owned reclamation farms in the tropical province
produced a record 208,000 tons of rubber in 1997, accounting for
90 percent of the island's output and half of the country's
total.
</P>
<P>
However, the income from rubber is expected to drop by 900
million yuan (108 million US dollars) because of excessive
imports. So, the central government decided to cut imports and buy
20,000 tons of rubber from Hainan to replenish state
reserves. 
</P>
