<TEXT>
<P>
LANZHOU, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Northwest China's Gansu Province
will host the 1998 Gansu-Lanzhou trade fair Aug. 26-30 this year.
</P>
<P>
The trade fair will emphasize introducing foreign investment,
seeking cooperative opportunities in various fields and presenting
a series of quality local products and tourism routes.
</P>
<P>
The fair will be the fifth of its kind held since 1991. The
previous fairs have helped accelerate the province's economic
development and opening-up to the outside.
</P>
