<HEADLINE> Increasing Gold Reserves In Northwestern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XINING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Recent gold discoveries in
northwest China's Qinghai Province mean that it is expected to be
a major gold production base in future, with reserves estimated at
300 to 350 tons.
</P>
<P>
The province produced 3,828 kg of gold last year, up
282 percent from 1996.
</P>
<P>
Qinghai plans to spend 440 million yuan increasing gold output
by 20 percent annually during the 1996-2000 period, according to
Ma Zhongqiu, director of the Provincial Gold Administration.
</P>
<P>
But, Ma says, because of insufficient prospecting, vast parts
of Qinghai have not been explored.
</P>
<P>
He says that developing gold resources in Qinghai is still
profitable, with the large amount of inexpensive labor. 
</P>
