<HEADLINE> Shandong Striving to Attract Overseas Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, March 3 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province has
published a wide range of preferential policies to encourage
overseas investors in specific fields.
</P>
<P>
According to local officials, overseas investors will be given
tax breaks and price cuts for the acquisition of land-use rights
if they invest in infrastructure projects, comprehensive
agricultural development projects, export-oriented farming or
high-tech projects.
</P>
<P>
The overseas investors will also be given other forms of
preferential treatment if they invest in technical upgrading of
local manufacturers or engage in the construction of
housing for families with low and middle incomes.
</P>
<P>
The move is designed to attract more overseas funds in
accordance with local conditions in this coastal province and help
it open wider to the outside world, officials said.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, the province had altogether approved
establishment of overseas-financed projects with contracts
involving an agreed use of 36.5 billion U.S. dollars of overseas
investment. And the actual paid-in sum of overseas investment
stands at 20.2 billion U.S. dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
