<HEADLINE> Italian, U.S. Computer Giants Mergeed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Computer giants Olivetti, of Italy,
and U.S. firm Wang Laboratories Inc. signed a merger agreement on
Monday, creating a Wang Global Corporation, whose annual sales are
expected to reach 3.6 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Wang Laboratories will spend 430 million
dollars to buy Olsy, an information service company attached to
Olivetti, which owns 39 percent of the new company.
</P>
<P>
Olsy, producing 60 percent of Olivetti's annual sales volume,
employs 12,000 people. Wang Laboratories employs 9,000 people, but
makes 1.35 billion dollars in sales.
</P>
<P>
Wang Global is the third joint venture Olivetti has
established. It has already set up a joint venture with Germany's
Mannesmann Corp. and another with Britain's Edward Gottesmann
Company. 
</P>
</TEXT>
