<HEADLINE> Costa Rica to Cut tariffs for Guatemalan Goods </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Costa Rica will soon cut tariffs
for Guatemalan oils and fats, the Costa Rican Ministry of Economy
said.
</P>
<P>
The measure was agreed last month during a Central American
Ministry Council Board in San Jose. It will end a trade war
between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Costa Rica imposed import duties of 5 to 15 percent on
Guatemalan oils and fats this year, saying that Guatemala was
exporting products made from raw materials bought from third
countries.
</P>
<P>
Guatemala retaliated on February 11 when it imposed a tariff of
17 percent on Costa Rican milk, chocolates and candies. 
</P>
