<HEADLINE> Kazakhstan Works to Attract Foreign Investment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ALMA ATA, March 2 (Xinhua) --Kazakhstan's President Nursultan
Nazarbayev said here Monday that the government must formulate
policies to protect the interests of foreign investors.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting of government officials and foreign enterprise
managers, Nazarbayev said foreign investment is vital to
Kazakhstan's economic construction, and attracting foreign
investment is a steadfast policy of the country.
</P>
<P>
On the whole, the investment condition has greatly improved in
Kazakhstan, said Nazarbayev. He admitted that foreign investors
still face many difficulties because of defects in the legal
system and the abuse of power by some officials.
</P>
<P>
The president severely criticized the government's absence of
alacrity in improving investment conditions. He vowed to curb the
misbehavior of government officials.
</P>
<P>
Government officials should meet and communicate with foreign
investors to help them succeed in business in Kazakhstan, the
president said.
</P>
<P>
More than 200 foreign companies have invested in
Kazakhstan. They have made tremendous contributions to the
economic development and social stability of the country.
</P>
<P>
Cabinet members, including Prime Minister Nurlan Balgimbaev and
First Deputy Prime Minister Alievich Djandosov, and administrative
officials of provincial and municipal governments of Kazakhstan
also attended the meeting. 
</P>
