<HEADLINE> Sweden, Austria Against NATO Membership </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Sweden and Austria should not
join the North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO), Austrian
Chancellor Viktor Klima and his Swedish counterpart, Goran
Persson, said after talks on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"We should instead set up a better European security
structure," said Persson and Klima jointly. "We could apply better
collaboration on foreign policies."
</P>
<P>
Austria will be the rotary presidency of the European Union
(EU) for the second half of the year. Talks between Klima, who was
visiting Sweden, and Persson focused on EU and European security
issues.
</P>
<P>
Cooperation on security policies will be conducted between the
two countries' ruling Social Democratic Parties.
</P>
<P>
Similar cooperation already exists between Austria and Finland,
whose Prime Minister Paavo Lipponen is to visit Vienna next week.
</P>
