<HEADLINE> More Sugar Mills Being Built in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Ten more sugar mills are being
built in the eastern and western parts of Myanmar's Bago mountain
range where there are enough sugarcane resources, The New Light of
Myanmar newspaper reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The sugar mills under construction by the Myanmar Sugarcane
Enterprise (MSE) of the Ministry of Agriculture and Irrigation
cover those in Paukkaung, Pyay and Aunglan in Bago and Magway
divisions.
</P>
<P>
Some of these on-going sugar mill projects are implemented by
companies from China and Thailand under contracts reached with the
MSE last year.
</P>
<P>
Myanmar has been striving to expand cultivation hectarage and
production of sugarcane, one of the four cash crops in addition to
paddy.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Myanmar registered an average
annual sugar output of 45,000 tons in recent years with a per
capita consumption of only 1.6 kilograms.
</P>
<P>
Latest statistics show that 30,134 tons of sugar were produced
in the first 10 months of 1997. 
</P>
