<HEADLINE> Blatter Guarantees More Tickets </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 2 (Xinhua) -- FIFA general secretary Sepp Blatter
promised that fans outside France would get more tickets for the
World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Blatter told German sports television DSF on Sunday that the
world soccer governing body had asked France for reserved tickets
for the retail market in France.
</P>
<P>
He said that would allow more tickets for the associations of
the countries in the finals, but he did not elaborate how many
tickets could be expected to get and which country is available
for the spare tickets.
</P>
<P>
The monopoly of the tickets selling by the French organising
committee (CFO) had been warned by the European Union but CFO and
FIFA claimed that their measures were following guidelines agreed
by the EU some two years ago.
</P>
<P>
But CFO and FIFA received rampant complains from national
soccer authorities for the unfair allocation of the ticketing.
</P>
