<HEADLINE> At Least 20 Killed in Traffic Accident in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 3 (Xinhua) -- At least 20 passengers were killed
and 20 others injured on Sunday when a bus plunged into the deep
water of a lake in Vietnam's central coast province of Binh Dinh,
said reports reaching here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The accident was described by the reports as one of Vietnam's
worst traffic accidents for years.
</P>
<P>
It occurred when the bus collided with a truck carrying cement,
sending it crashing through the safety rail of a bridge into the
lake.
</P>
<P>
Some 50 passengers were confirmed saved, but the reports vary
on how many people were aboard the bus when it crashed, with
survivors estimated between 70 and 100. 
</P>
