<HEADLINE> Brief Latin-American News </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, March 2 (Xinhua) --
</P>
<P>
High Costs on Argentinian Credit Cards
</P>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- Credit card holders in Argentina are having to
pay a monthly commission of 4 percent.
</P>
<P>
There are 7.5 million credit cards circulating in
Argentina. The average per capita expenditure is about 400 pesos
(400 U.S. dollars) a month, which means an average commission fee
of 17 pesos (17 U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Chile Exports Less Fruit to Latin America
</P>
<P>
SANTIAGO -- Chile's export of fruit to Latin American countries
fell by 15.5 percent between September 1997 and February this
year, compared with the same period of the previous year.
</P>
<P>
According to statistics from the Chilean Exporters Association,
Chile exported more than 11.5 million boxes in the 1995-96 period,
but only 9.7 million boxes this year.
</P>
<P>
It said that the main regional markets for Chilean fruits are
Brazil, Argentina and Mexico.
</P>
<P>
Nicaraguan Machine Exports to Reach 300 Million Dollars this
</P>
<P>
Year
</P>
<P>
MANAGUA -- Machine exports in Nicaragua will exceed 300 million
dollars this year, 30 percent up from 1997, said the
administration of free economic zones.
</P>
<P>
With the opening of three private free economic zones, some
20,000 jobs are expected to be created in 1998. Most factories
operating in free zones mainly produce textile machines.
</P>
<P>
Poultry Exports Decline in Brazil
</P>
<P>
BRASILIA -- The volume of Brazilian poultry exports fell by 31
percent in January this year against the same month of 1997, the
Brazilian Association of Poultry Exporters and Producers said.
</P>
<P>
It said that the Asian financial crisis is the major cause for
the sharp decline.
</P>
<P>
Mexico Becomes World's Largest Lemon Producer
</P>
<P>
MEXICO CITY -- Mexico has become the largest lemon producer in
the world with an annual harvest of more than 300 thousand tons,
general manager of the state company "Citricos de Guerrero" Luis
Figuero said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
