<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russia Calls for Dialogue on Kosovo Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The Russian Foreign Ministry called
on Yugoslav authorities and ethnic Albanian leaders to show
restraint and start talking to end the conflict in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
In a statement on Monday, the ministry voiced deep concern over
the tense situation in Kosovo and condemned terrorist actions
there.
</P>
<P>
The statement urged both sides of the conflict to abandon their
use of force. It called for a settlement of the Kosovo issue on
the principle of maintaining the integrity of Yugoslavia and
respecting the rights of ethnic Albanians in Kosovo.
</P>
<P>
The ethnic Albanian community, which accounts for 90 percent of
the population of Kosovo, has been seeking independence for the
province from the Republic of Serbia in Yugoslavia. This has been
resolutely opposed by the Yugoslavian authorities.
</P>
<P>
In recent months, separatists have carried out terrorist
actions in the province. A Yugoslav Interior Ministry police
patrol was ambushed last Saturday in Glovgovac, Kosovo, resulting
in the death of four policemen and 16 attackers. 
</P>
</TEXT>
