<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0276 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia's Monthly Inflation Hits 12.76 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Rising commodity prices pushed
Indonesia's monthly inflation rate to 12.76 percent in February,
the highest in the 30 years of President Soeharto's government,
the Central Bureau of Statistics (BPS) said.
</P>
<P>
The February inflation rate doubled the January level of 6.88
percent, and increased 12 times compared to the 1.05 percent in
February last year.
</P>
<P>
Accordingly, inflation rate for the first two months of 1998
was 19.64 percent.
</P>
<P>
In February, food prices increased 16.07 percent, housing by
10.03 percent, clothing by 15.62 percent and miscellaneous goods
and services by 9.31 percent, the figures issued by BPS Monday
showed.
</P>
<P>
Inflation rate started to increase significantly in September
last year at 1.29 percent as the currency woes, which first hit
the country in July, began to take effect.
</P>
<P>
At present, the rupiah (national currency) is trading at 8,500
against U.S. dollar. Early July last year it traded at 2,400 per
dollar. The currency dropped to its lowest level of 17,00 to the
dollar in January.
</P>
</TEXT>
