<HEADLINE> Ukraine, Macedonia Sign Cooperation Treaty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Ukrainian Foreign Minister Gennady
Udovenko and his Macedonian counterpart Blagoi Handziski signed
treaties here Monday to encourage friendship and cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The two foreign ministers also signed agreements to avoid
double taxation and to promote and protect mutual investments.
</P>
<P>
At a news conference following the signing ceremony, Udovenko
said the two countries would cooperate in construction,
transportation, heavy industry and the metallurgical industry.
</P>
<P>
Ukraine and Macedonia should also stimulate their economic and
trade cooperation, Udovenko said. The annual trade volume between
the two countries is about 50 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Handziski said both countries support the establishment of a
new trans-Atlantic security system and have agree to formulate
treaties and agreements to boost their relations.
</P>
<P>
Handziski, who arrived here Sunday for a four-day visit, has
also met with Ukrainian President Leonid Danilovich and Prime
Minister valery Pustovoitenko. 
</P>
