<DOCNO> XIE19980303.0285 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Guangdong Rectifies Fraudulent Foreign Exchange Settlements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, March 3 (Xinhua) -- Guangdong province has improved
its foreign exchange operations by strengthening the battle
against malpractices related to foreign exchange settlement.
</P>
<P>
Guangdong banks recorded a favorable foreign exchange sales and
purchases balance of 217 million US dollars in 1997, thereby
reversing a long-standing unfavorable situation.
</P>
<P>
Since last June, provincial foreign exchange control
authorities have initiated special audits of 123 banks responsible
for foreign exchange transaction. Banks found in violation of
relevant rules have been subject to appropriate action.
</P>
<P>
The campaign also resulted in the seizure of 4,458 false
customs declaration forms used by enterprises to evade export
rebates.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises failing to report foreign exchange revenues from
exports were subject to administrative restrictions including
the inability to receive required export documents. A total of 68
enterprises were subject to related administrative procedures
during the year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
