<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-03 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Southwest China Province Developing Tourism Facilities </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUNMING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- About 420 million yuan will be
invested in developing tourism facilities this year in
Xishuangbanna, a scenic spot in southwest China's Yunnan Province.
</P>
<P>
Situated in the southernmost part of Yunnan, Xishuangbanna is
the only oasis in the Tropic of Cancer boasting such a wide
variety of plant and animal life.
</P>
<P>
Together with its ethnic colors, the area attracts a large
number of tourists. In 1997, 1.8 million tourists visited
Xishuangbanna, more than double the number of local residents.
</P>
<P>
An official from the local tourism department said the funds
will be spent on six projects including road reconstruction to
improve traffic conditions as well as new parks. All of these
projects should be completed in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Xishuangbanna has the largest variety of plants and animals in
the country. To let more tourists enjoy the attractive scenery,
Xishuangbanna will build a tropical plant park covering 80
hectares.
</P>
<P>
Other facilities such as an animal exhibition center and
butterfly park will be constructed.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
