<HEADLINE> Rafter Scraps Through in Rotterdam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, March 2 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Patrick Rafter of
Australia scraped through the first round of the Rotterdam World
Indoor tennis tournament, scoring a comeback win over Dutchman
Peter Wessels on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, the world number three, avoided a rout after first set
down, edging 5-7, 7-6 (7-3), 6-1 against the 218th-ranked
wild-card opponent.
</P>
<P>
With a 4-5 deficit in the second set, Rafter, the U.S. Open
champion last year, found his form and broke back to save his
match.
</P>
<P>
In other matches, third-seeded Briton Greg Rusedski needed
three tie-breaks against Moroccan Karim Alami to advance 6-7, 7-6,
7-6, and sixth-seeded Spaniard Sergi Bruguera beat Alami's
compatriot Hicham Arazi 7-6, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Former Wimbledon champion Richard Krajicek, who won here last
year, beat Dutch compatriot Dennis van Scheppingen 7-5, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
Marc Rosset of Switzerland was the only seed dropped after
Monday's matches. He withdrew due to a flu. 
</P>
</TEXT>
