<HEADLINE> China's Passenger Traffic Volume Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- China's passenger traffic
volume increased to 4.5 billion persons during the first eleven
months in 1997, up two percent on an annual basis, according to
the latest statistics from the State Statistics Bureau.
</P>
<P>
The passenger traffic volume of the railway sector reached 846
million persons, down 2.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
That of motor vehicles was 3.5 billion persons, up 3.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
That of civil aviation was 52 million persons, up 1.2
percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
