<HEADLINE> New Aviation Venture Set up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- A new joint venture was set up
Monday by China National South Aero-Engine Company (SAEC) and Pratt &AMP;
Whitney Canada, according to today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The Southern Pratt &AMP; Whitney Aero-Engine Company Ltd,
involving a total investment of over 27 million US dollars, will
manufacture gas turbine engine components for the Pratt &AMP; Whitney
Canada.
</P>
<P>
As China's leading small gas turbine engine manufacturer, the
SAEC will hold a majority of 51 percent of ownership share.
</P>
<P>
The venture, to be located in Zhuzhou, Hunan Province, is
expected to begin production next year.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-based daily noted cooperation will promote the
development of the two firms in one of the world's fastest
growing civil aviation markets.
</P>
<P>
A few more similar joint ventures will be set up later this
year, said the paper, adding that the long-awaited decision on the AE100
airliner project is expected to be reached by the end of this
month.
</P>
<P>
The Pratt &AMP; Whitney Canada, a world leader in the production of
gas turbine engines for the general aviation and helicopter
markets, is a subsidiary of United Technologies Corporation of
Hartford, Connecticut. 
</P>
</TEXT>
