<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Bank to Bolster China's Aerospace Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 3 (Xinhua) -- The Export and Import Bank of
China (Eximbank) has signed a package of agreements to provide up
to four billion yuan in export seller's credits within three years
to the China Great Wall Industry Corp (CGWIC), according to
today's China Daily.
</P>
<P>
The CGWIC can use the funds to engage in satellite launching
business along with the relevant export of machinery and
electronic products.
</P>
<P>
The loans would help enhance China's competitiveness in the
world's satellite launching market, promote the country's
export of machinery and electronic products, and boost trade
in technology services.
</P>
<P>
The agreements will enable the bank to simplify procedures
involved in project assessments and guarantees, based on the good
credit standing of CGWIC, while providing timely credit to the
enterprise.
</P>
<P>
CGWIC will follow the agreements to pay the due loan principle
and interest of Eximbank's loans, thus maintaining its credit
while continuing to apply for loans form the bank.
</P>
<P>
Eximbank, one of the country's policy-oriented banks
established in 1994, serves to assist the export of high-tech,
high value-added products.
</P>
<P>
The CGWIC, the nation's sole company authorized to conduct
commercial satellite launching services for foreign countries, has
so far carried out 48 satellite launcheds, of which 42 have been
successful. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
