urban market this year, according to the All-China Federation of
Supply and Marketing Cooperatives.
</P>
<P>
The country's rural markets will further demonstrate their
vitality and potentials this year by growing about 10 percent over
last year's 1.04 trillion yuan (125.89 billion US dollars), said
Ma Lisheng, deputy director of the federation.  
