<HEADLINE> UEFA Giver Full Support to Johansson FIFA Bid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 2 (Xinhua) -- European soccer governing body UEFA
confirmed on Monday it give its full support to Lennart Johansson
in his bid for the FIFA presidency.
</P>
<P>
The confirmation was a move designed to end rumours of a split
among its members in the build-up to the election in June.
</P>
<P>
The eight members of UEFA's executive committee, who are also
members of FIFA's executive committee, said they wanted Sepp
Blatter, FIFA'S secretary-general to say once and for all next
week whether or not he was standing for the presidency and end
weeks of rumour about his intentions.
</P>
<P>
The European members of FIFA's executive committee plus four
members from Africa and one from Oceania have called for an
extraordinary meeting of the FIFA executive committee in Zurich on
March 13 with just one topic on the agenda -- Blatter's position
in the presidential race.
</P>
<P>
While UEFA itself is technically at least not directly involved
in the election, their eight FIFA members have repeatedly said
that Blatter should not run for the presidency if he remains in
his post as FIFA's secretary-general.
</P>
<P>
Antonio Matarrese of Italy, who is also a FIFA vice-president,
said on Monday that Johansson, the UEFA president, had the full
backing of the entire executive which appeared to end rumours that
Switzerland might break ranks with UEFA and back Blatter. 
</P>
</TEXT>
