<HEADLINE> U.S. Says Iran's Opposition to Terrorism "Encouraging" </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The United States said on
Monday it was encouraged by Iran's statement of opposing
terrorism.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian statement was reported by Italian Foreign
Minister Lamberto Dini, who is on a visit to Tehran.
</P>
<P>
U.S. State Department spokesman James Rubin said the
statement was "encouraging to us."
</P>
<P>
"Foreign Minister Dini has described his discussion with
(Iranian) President (Mohhamad) Khatami in encouraging terms --
namely that the government of Iran has indicated that it opposes
terrorism," he told reporters. "This is encouraging to us."
</P>
<P>
Dini, the first cabinet-rank official to visit Iran since the
European Union lifted a ban last week on high-level visits, said
the United States would be pushed by the realities of Gulf
politics to pursue a more normal relationship with Iran.
</P>
<P>
Rubin said Secretary of State Madeleine Albright would likely
raise with Dini his thoughts on the visit when she travels to
Rome later in the week.  
