<HEADLINE> Albright Plans Trip to Ukraine, NATO Allies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 2 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright will discuss the Iraqi situation and other
issues on a trip starting Thursday to Ukraine, Italy, Germany,
France, Britain and Canada.
</P>
<P>
"The two-fold purpose of her trip will be to maintain our close
relationship with some of our strongest allies... and to nurture
our relationship with a new and important partner, Ukraine,"
announced State Department spokesman James Rubin.
</P>
<P>
Albright is expected to examine closely with members of the
North Atlantic Treaty Organization (NATO) the agreement signed
last week between Iraqi authorities and U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan, Rubin said.
</P>
<P>
Albright's first stop will be Ukraine. She and Ukrainian
President Leonid Kuchma will discuss nonproliferation concerns and
the business and investment climate in Ukraine.
</P>
<P>
During her visit to Italy, Albright will go to the Vatican for
a discussion with Pope John Paul II on his recent trip to Cuba and
other issues.
</P>
<P>
From Europe, she will travel to Ottawa, Canada, for meetings
with Canadian leaders. "She will follow up on discussions with the
Canadian government from the APEC (Asian Pacific Economic
Cooperation forum) meeting," said Rubin. 
</P>
</TEXT>
