<HEADLINE> German Public Sector Workers Stage Mass Protests </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, March 2 (Xinhua) -- More than 60,000 public sector
workers throughout Germany took part in warning strikes Monday to
press their demands for wage increases and job security.
</P>
<P>
The mass protests Monday had caused traffic chaos, school
suspension, and delays in garbage collection in about 150 German
cities, reports reaching here said.
</P>
<P>
Demonstrators asked the government to meet their demand for a
4.5 percent wage increase as well as to drop a plan to cut sick
pay and pension benefits.
</P>
<P>
According to the German trade union for public services OETV,
further protests which could involve 80,000 workers are planned
before a decisive round of wage talks with the government Tuesday
and Wednesday. 
</P>
