<HEADLINE> United States Urges Suharto to Press for Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 2 (Xinhua) -- The United States on Monday
urged Indonesian President Suharto to press for implementation
of International Monetary Fund economic reform.
</P>
<P>
"President Suharto should place his full authority and the
full authority of his office behind the economic reforms that he
has agreed to," White House Press Secretary Mike McCurry told
reporters at a briefing.
</P>
<P>
"That's the way in which you can restore economic stability,"
he said.
</P>
<P>
He said former Vice President Walter Mondale, President Bill
Clinton's special envoy to Indonesia, would tell Suharto that
"full implementation" of the IMF program was essential.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, U.S. Treasury Secretary Robert Rubin said Mondale's
mission to Indonesia was to continue previous talks between
Clinton and Suharto, but not to ask President Suharto to step
down.  
</P>
